parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission warning light turns on
the vehicle slows down or loses power
the transmission makes a whining or grinding noise
the vehicle stalls or becomes stuck in gear
and the vehicle may not accelerate or move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
and the vehicle may not accelerate or move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power train can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The power train warning light turns on
the vehicle slows down or loses power
the power train makes a whining or grinding noise
the vehicle stalls or becomes stuck in gear
and the vehicle may not accelerate or move.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the subframe and suspension can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Rattling sound
clunking noise
loss of steering control
unpredictable steering
difficulty driving
and warning lights may appear on the dashboard.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The overheating of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Transmission overheating light appears on the dashboard
loss of acceleration
and difficulty maintaining speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lower Control Arm and Ball Joint Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the lower control arm and ball joint can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: Clunking noise
popping or snapping sound
and difficulty driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the subframe can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle's front wheels buckle outward
the steering wheel locks up
the vehicle pulls to one side
and there may be a loud banging or popping noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels loose or difficult to turn
the steering wheel locks up
and there may be a loud popping or cracking noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shuts off or loses power while driving
the transmission slips or hesitates
and there may be a whining or grinding noise.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to lose power, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The instrument panel lights turn off
the horn malfunctions
and there may be other electrical system failures.
